data.name: coreEloCacheTextBox.ToolTip
data.value: Enter the time in minutes to cache QLRanks Elo results. This will allow Elo look-ups to occur much faster since the Elo data will be saved and SST will not have to constantly access the QLRanks website.

data.name: coreOwnerNameLabel.ToolTip
data.value: Enter the bot owner(s) QL account name(s). If there is more than one owner, enter each name, one per line. Users with owner privileges have full control over SST; this should not be given out freely.

data.name: coreHideQlConsoleCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Select whether you want to hide ALL QL console text. Note: SST uses QL debug text to get information, which can send a lot of text to the console. Disabling this will disable all console text, not just debug info (same as con_noprint 1)

data.name: modAutoVoterContainingTextBox.ToolTip
data.value: Specify an optional parameter. For example, if you selected "kick", then here you can specify the name of a player; or if you selected "teamsize", then you could specify the # of players. Votes matching this will be automatically passed or rejected. Note: If you leave this blank, then ALL votes of that type will be passed or rejected.

data.name: modEloLimiterMaxEloTextBox.ToolTip
data.value: (Optional) Enter the maximum QLRanks Elo for your server. Any accounts that do not meet the minimum Elo OR have an Elo that is greater than this maximum value will be kicked when they attempt to connect to your server.

data.name: banMDelExpiredBansButton.ToolTip
data.value: Click this button to manually remove any expired bans. Note, expired bans are automatically removed by SST at various times, for example, an expired ban will be auto-removed when a banned player connects.
